mas"/><category term="ALEUTIA"/><category term="Deltatronic"/><category term="ID-Cooling"/><category term="Maczon"/><category term="Samsung"/><category term="A-TECH FABRICATION"/><category term="Calyos"/><category term="FSP"/><category term="Fanless Made Easy"/><category term="HFX"/><category term="Morex"/><category term="QUIETTY"/><category term="RASPBERRY PI"/><category term="Realan"/><category term="VIA"/><category term="ANTEC"/><category term="Azulle"/><category term="Chieftec"/><category term="LINUTOP"/><category term="Meanwhile in Russia"/><category term="QUANMAX"/><category term="SAPPHIRE"/><category term="SILVERPOWER"/><category term="Stealth"/><category term="Todd Lindström"/><category term="you&#39;re doing it wrong"/><category term="ADLINK"/><category term="ADVANTECH"/><category term="ASKTech"/><category term="COMMELL"/><category term="Chillblast"/><category term="Classy fanless setup"/><category term="Communication Technology"/><category term="CompTake"/><category term="EMKO"/><category term="EPoX"/><category term="Enermax"/><category term="GENESI"/><category term="GIGAIPC"/><category term="Gateway"/><category term="Gumstix"/><category term="HTPC.JP"/><category term="Haxx"/><category term="KEP Marine"/><category term="LANNER"/><category term="Lian Li"/><category term="M3cases"/><category term="MIFcom"/><category term="MITXPC"/><category term="MK802"/><category term="Myth debunked"/><category term="NEXCOM"/><category term="NFC"/><category term="OMAP"/><category term="POKINI"/><category term="POWERCOLOR"/><category term="Reeven"/><category term="Solid-Run"/><category term="Spire"/><category term="Star Metronic"/><category term="Supermicro"/><category term="TRAVLA"/><category term="ThermoLab"/><category term="Viako"/><category term="ViewSonic"/><category term="Wibtek"/><category term="Xigmatek"/><title type='text'>FanlessTech</title><subtitle type='html'></subtitle><link rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#feed' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/feeds/posts/default'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/'/><link rel='hub' href='http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/'/><link rel='next' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default?start-index=26&amp;max-results=25'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><generator version='7.00' uri='http://www.blogger.com'>Blogger</generator><openSearch:totalResults>3193</openSearch:totalResults><openSearch:startIndex>1</openSearch:startIndex><openSearch:itemsPerPage>25</openSearch:itemsPerPage><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-4845188550855755244</id><published>2026-04-13T12:58:00.001+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-13T12:58:22.892+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="ZOTAC"/><title type='text'>Discounted ZBOX with AirJet</title><summary type="text">The ZOTAC ZBOX PI430AJ is the only mini PC that replaces traditional cooling fans with two AirJet solid-state cooling modules. Despite its pocket-sized dimensions, the device packs an Intel Core i3-N300 processor and ultra-thin membranes to dissipate heat without any moving parts. It is technically fanless. This innovative design allows the system to remain (mostly) silent while sustaining peak </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4845188550855755244'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4845188550855755244'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/discounted-zbox-with-airjet.html' title='Discounted ZBOX with AirJet'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjsa1xoVahi_mupna1hp145rdn61iSqf_Dp8rqMyyvKHG_v-Aq_8RAQSwQ1njFT-okCEg6Y6GORsCD-XSD2BNnGEPx_R36MPu1pVVA8mc-a9ZQvR3T4G6qQlKt0xITkc3bsumJTTFibDbPmManOZMnHAX4z1qiEap007ntDhZKUh-hPF-oi8qUTRtIZEpw/s72-w400-h213-c/zbox3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-5883524796230183652</id><published>2026-04-10T00:02:00.003+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-10T06:32:23.088+02:00</updated><title type='text'>Fanless PCs, now in color</title><summary type="text">At just 82 x 82mm (3 x 3-inch) the Kubb Mini is one of the smallest passively-cooled PCs on the market. Powered via USB-C, the 500g cube comes with the Intel N150 or N300 processor, 16GB of RAM and a 256GB&amp;nbsp;NVMe&amp;nbsp;SSD. Connectivity includes dual HDMI 2.0 ports, Ethernet, and Wi-Fi 6. The Kubb Mini is available in vibrant colors starting at €430.https://kubb.eu/en/1-mini-pc-kubb-mini.html</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5883524796230183652'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5883524796230183652'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/fanless-pcs-now-in-color.html' title='Fanless PCs, now in color'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhYcCukop4G0T76UGUTmtfDXZPW2ZKG-szul7nljONmUDZVbKaSwIcqlMx76Ysdb9WYoH6mBCmv6kiqUNf0iwMEQNTm3AcXWAe18SwmfjZYWqDWseOPiIvBJTSr9nwWLCMrfZ2y_w535VblVjVj9eg9tZpyo4yJnDOBKVqJ-Oc2qd1J90hT1258qEO74V4/s72-c/kubb4.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2591539705035823149</id><published>2026-04-09T13:03:00.005+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-09T18:11:09.661+02:00</updated><title type='text'>AAEON&#39;s new Twin Lake offering</title><summary type="text">The&amp;nbsp;AAEON TWL01 Edge is powered by the Intel Twin Lake processors and is designed for high-efficiency edge computing or digital signage. It&#39;s also available to the general public and could be used as a reliable first computer for kids, or a web browsing station for seniors. It supports dual 4K displays via two HDMI 2.0b ports. Other specs are a little depressing with just 8GB of RAM and 64GB</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2591539705035823149'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2591539705035823149'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/aaeons-new-twin-lake-offering.html' title='AAEON&#39;s new Twin Lake offering'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhvpgey-ycQdv6sxCYI2-v21CmAUMOQgSnZVFBc7WPkjEB3KMavLfEjnjc_PyauNtD-jVFT7IzbmDN2Phpm9Pjwrfo1COWJCu-RD5lLACUunx3hAgNHOvqUPSWZqBbrUsYtp_BUb7ZZmIyUPMwakj4Mnmacq3eVXwCGkfCOaAX5DSmcy5rsQ28-GbdYLt0/s72-c/intelli.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-8048150706738772552</id><published>2026-04-08T12:27:00.006+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-09T07:16:58.284+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>About the Arctic Senza PC</title><summary type="text">A lot of you have been asking about Arctic’s Senza under-desk mount, which contradicts our core recommendations for passive cooling and convection. While we do like the hardware itself, we only recommend wall-mounting the Senza to ensure unobstructed airflow (pictured). Special thanks to Arctic for their commitment to fanless PCs, and good luck to the Senza AI 370.</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/8048150706738772552'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/8048150706738772552'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/about-arctic-senza-pc.html' title='About the Arctic Senza PC'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgn_TqovNhx_yLDZiRq_1Dc7ZQMqhQmwa2x75kQXg1796eGiIGX3rRwzcHSBCAyNFRt40oQxKUb-ysBUezo8-DMTnlQ7BKhTN3MB_Fw5e6ZwPdXEeeg6uyXK_WCFZLjB-iHVP6vZ0TlE27mTc4p7FmDLQ1-Fcv0gKh-LZ-whhMD6ybjK7MJFQ6__qiD4_I/s72-w474-h474-c/Senza.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-4283088181479769260</id><published>2026-04-07T13:01:00.002+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-07T17:41:23.380+02:00</updated><title type='text'>The AI bubble is real</title><summary type="text">The new Dell Pro Micro Thin Client is a compact, secure endpoint designed for virtual environments, featuring Intel N-series processors ranging from the N150 to the N350. The passively-cooled and very stylish 182 x 178 x 36mm unit supports up to two 4K displays, and runs on either Dell ThinOS 10 or Windows 11 IoT Enterprise. Unfortunately, Dell is asking&amp;nbsp;nearly $1,000 for a system featuring </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4283088181479769260'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4283088181479769260'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/the-ai-bubble-is-real.html' title='The AI bubble is real'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhGikZEtsaVY9xNkNqJha9r0G5aqwYs-D9FdpujvKeZZzSeEASX5VNeYaSghoWuczGQ8a9BOhEfJsNTfep_8Sfgz14nMWWWwkCu-Zx8xcp8gdvnnoYwW5K3Un2qUGJX7FPcmYfvhwu8ZCrpn9tniJ4AAgK7RK-QkGOoeUZrRx2WHRPhTLhAurPggvIU8P0/s72-c/dell3.png" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-4402112547991863151</id><published>2026-04-06T20:00:00.001+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-06T20:00:46.847+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>Arctic Senza AI 370 installation guide</title><summary type="text">Courtesy of ARCTIC</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4402112547991863151'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/4402112547991863151'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/arctic-senza-ai-370-installation-guide.html' title='Arctic Senza AI 370 installation guide'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://img.youtube.com/vi/cS7wSEcOmic/default.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-174375698156791413</id><published>2026-04-03T00:07:00.003+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-03T00:24:55.918+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="AKASA"/><title type='text'>Akasa Kepler 2U case available</title><summary type="text">Akasa&#39;s 2U rackmount fanless case is now available as a standalone product or as a complete PC. Designed to support Micro-ATX and Mini-ITX motherboards with Intel LGA1851 and LGA1700 sockets. It features a robust cooling system to dissipate heat from processors up to 35W TDP. The front panel features four 2.5&quot; SATA SSD/HDD hot-swappable drive bays with secure locks and dual USB 3.2 Gen 1 ports. </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/174375698156791413'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/174375698156791413'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/akasa-kepler-2u-case-available.html' title='Akasa Kepler 2U case available'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj_ZC5EAwnykaDVwunttk78OelKHiWs5hagxsBPRWC5BAfk2mNR6ezhjhqFnZIBPTp8tsliS7GT4IOKdzF1TDz66Ftits_h5lX0eewF8UiCbfHBkHxIBEuixEGoeNU08WpdnC3l7OTXT6ig4dluc_CD3btEw_mqQT7phWk0pjNKK-5YQJo7PCfZ1e94Tzs/s72-w400-h170-c/Kepler3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-5606190459830453512</id><published>2026-04-02T15:20:00.001+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-02T15:20:38.238+02:00</updated><title type='text'>Passively-cooled Bitcoin miner</title><summary type="text">Source:&amp;nbsp;Bitaxe</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5606190459830453512'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5606190459830453512'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/passively-cooled-bitcoin-miner.html' title='Passively-cooled Bitcoin miner'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEg5DP7DDHqyGyoWhQya_IZqamDcf_h25GL-tK2pMRWf9cccqiFRwtpLW5JXvNzhZFnT-HK7Aar4ces9EtcOC11ljuqjkDcVLiKNmPpHfkYdIVk_6lDhP73qRsv0ZI3DTTk2fquoazcXUMS8UVclTRrDBN_xRNtvDvafmP0zQU7jSAxQqwLJN-z1rM4u0qg/s72-c/Bitaxe1.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-3709580188705562824</id><published>2026-04-01T00:02:00.001+02:00</published><updated>2026-04-01T00:02:17.873+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Noctua"/><title type='text'>This fanless CPU cooler blew my mind</title><summary type="text">Courtesy of Mr Matt Lee</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/3709580188705562824'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/3709580188705562824'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/04/this-fanless-cpu-cooler-blew-my-mind.html' title='This fanless CPU cooler blew my mind'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://img.youtube.com/vi/9BpIaJQqc-Q/default.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2719597584556231123</id><published>2026-03-31T00:05:00.002+02:00</published><updated>2026-03-31T00:07:12.554+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>Quality thermal pads are a rare commodity</title><summary type="text">There&#39;s something special about the&amp;nbsp;ARCTIC TP-3&amp;nbsp;thermal pad. Based on a proprietary silicone formula, it offers excellent thermal conductivity while remaining electrically non-conductive and non-capacitive. Its soft, squeezable texture allows it to mold perfectly to components, making it a user-friendly alternative to traditional thermal pastes on VRMs, RAM chips, or M.2 SSDs. The </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2719597584556231123'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2719597584556231123'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/quality-thermal-pads-are-rare-commodity.html' title='Quality thermal pads are a rare commodity'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjC0rMjw_6O1LHPtkWP9NCeHV8tiRYiCwJDFj2gUeSIid3OWqKLHPt6sFikuipXfKQK6gQHrMfuwWQer80bbkyarQOtqYDZzJkmGZTiemAZWEbrJY-DMydGKbsl-c4CmdyjEycP6GldNn60JhaQZL1GAWPABOGJTdLh5Lxrx_8QsHFNTy7vpXUHlIXk58g/s72-c/pads3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2284671344569989019</id><published>2026-03-30T12:51:00.002+02:00</published><updated>2026-03-30T12:51:23.815+02:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="ASRock"/><title type='text'>Minimalist homelab</title><summary type="text">&quot;I&#39;m just running a very modest homelab server for music streaming purposes thanks to Navidrome. It&#39;s totally fanless ! There is a small TP-LINK switch (2 ethernet ports) at the back of the PC. It runs on Windows 10 IoT Enterprise LTSC. Why ? Before, I was running Ubuntu Server (much better) but had many freezes... I didn&#39;t know at the time that the second ram slot was the culprit... Instead of </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2284671344569989019'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2284671344569989019'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/minimalist-homelab.html' title='Minimalist homelab'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjPt9-TT8cVCFWF0yvAKbmeFbtt1E7_MHhMJ2T5SG1CXWni2ih3f8C_-D20gBUt7d0NzYwKNFrwbRl3c3EKe9D_Uw_3d-sasQG_GAKD6Yd68AuPgEKsLfBqj17f0hs0uzX1diWXPMpwBubm3-aFmG-UGwg-ZLY9VuNlcgMtAzSdK4nBo4KV6U6TM9vXNMc/s72-w300-h400-c/homelab1.webp" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-552495647823308421</id><published>2026-03-27T00:13:00.003+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-27T09:22:58.574+01:00</updated><title type='text'>DIY fanless LarkBox update</title><summary type="text">Remember this passively-cooled CHUWI mini PC&amp;nbsp;from 2020? It shipped with the right processor and an old Zalman chipset cooler was used to handle the 10W&amp;nbsp;Celeron J4125. Here is it today (second picture). It&#39;s still working beautifully, and in total silence. Proving once again that fanless is the way to go (and that dust is not a problem).&amp;nbsp;Source:&amp;nbsp;Hydrosaure&amp;nbsp;</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/552495647823308421'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/552495647823308421'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/diy-fanless-larkbox-update.html' title='DIY fanless LarkBox update'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhfOifLrbdMn4b1RpgiD7q7ZnjoKeJGteLq1Flx3zoCfl492Jb7GHoAPBIQasizgi7_UoWP13pJ7K5rmd4_fA2dytevQw7fXjhJ4s3GarP87WxAbbsntkp66DQJaMHhXf0N4FtTzr-lcCBaDLu7M4U_L-cUDaBMIKplPkZvZfn6hpeQklgrU2mkDst10pg/s72-w300-h400-c/larkbox3.jpeg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-5572869320040584853</id><published>2026-03-26T00:03:00.002+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-26T00:09:13.182+01:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="OnLogic"/><title type='text'>OnLogic CL260 in action</title><summary type="text">Learn more about the CL260 here.</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5572869320040584853'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5572869320040584853'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/onlogic-cl260-in-action.html' title='OnLogic CL260 in action'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://img.youtube.com/vi/AYncpF2GHtw/default.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2712091668089585193</id><published>2026-03-25T01:21:00.002+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-25T07:00:41.003+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Odroid H4 cooling upgrade</title><summary type="text">Instead of using the stock cooler, this&amp;nbsp;Level1Techs&amp;nbsp;forum member mounts the Odroid H4 board inside a significantly larger aluminum case that acts as a giant heatsink. The Odroid H4 is very efficient, but under sustained high loads, the stock cooler can heat up fast. By using a case with a much higher thermal mass, it takes significantly longer for the system to reach peak temperature.&amp;</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2712091668089585193'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2712091668089585193'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/odroid-h4-cooling-upgrade.html' title='Odroid H4 cooling upgrade'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEg7y_5yZtJ4b8UqeTPIIlJimQl2ihRJEop6n7WnwrPw6RFVRKaVUBPoWvYkMHMCwrE1TBxmVPpLLG-FpSVC-lmQQFOZGYIIx1zZvYdn3VcJRB0XemmbN0Qjc84mHUZdC5p9M0jbY1x32jOqlHtQlkMmSeVPJblJFk61UOdr5FfEnFeYjKl4a1ElMa2s-lo/s72-c/odroid3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-1562018557522686861</id><published>2026-03-24T07:22:00.005+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-24T07:26:10.390+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Fanless A18 Mac Neo concept</title><summary type="text">We have a love hate relationship with Apple, but clearly, the latest MacBook Neo&amp;nbsp;is a stroke of genius. This Mac Neo concept is designed as a more affordable, colorful alternative to the Mac Mini, aimed at students and first-time buyers. Powered by the A18 Pro chip, the device utilizes a slim aluminum chassis and passive cooling. With a theoretical starting price of $399, this Mac Neo would </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/1562018557522686861'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/1562018557522686861'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/fanless-a18-mac-neo-concept.html' title='Fanless A18 Mac Neo concept'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgdp0WEh19BDsfyQcuKH-NtWrhZFS0KLQul0GbDKI6bigM3tG-uLSzyIIwh9J2piTpvxm9CK6lxQDYxD3TvqPzxfKLsEYToKa6qfQPZTWVeyiA36mXzN5v6QjVpP0Hxj_KEkC5allqdt1-z3gue_oyvDlNhVl9ibvyBJag_2anNq32QiYe2o8z8OD8ES90/s72-c/apple_mac_neo_1.webp" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2565382320149401962</id><published>2026-03-23T01:30:00.000+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-23T01:30:07.728+01:00</updated><title type='text'>This perfect cube is a Ryzen AI PC</title><summary type="text">The new KUBB is powered by AMD, and it&#39;s available in Europe now. The awfully cute 120 x 120mm PC&amp;nbsp;features a 100% silent design using a 1.4kg machined aluminum block as a heat sink (heavier than the massive Noctua NH-P1). At the heart of the PC is an AMD Ryzen processor (Ryzen AI 5 340 and Ryzen AI 7 350 options) that includes a dedicated Neural Processing Unit to accelerate AI-driven tasks </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2565382320149401962'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2565382320149401962'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/this-perfect-cube-is-ryzen-ai-pc.html' title='This perfect cube is a Ryzen AI PC'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjP4c8uLqgkqNV0RiH4-AuzXmL3PUhDqatt6oQwMAU79CYY0a96JD93Rk9t607O4Q5KCBF3LyAAMAeho-mHgUxk1cLY-NKcsZ7aOaLQhAJ_z9VBop0Q9ZW1wO8R6ZdcRYDMpj3Ld_9bwpN_rlhd1Zha_soll9TfgLJknj8JGUJNIMuwaRBUfbe3fVj3z7w/s72-c/kubb3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-7825203710022156460</id><published>2026-03-20T08:34:00.000+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-20T08:34:01.568+01:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>Arctic Senza AI 370 review</title><summary type="text">According to SweClockers, despite being fanless, the Ryzen AI 9 HX 370 computer performs impressively. It is roughly 50% faster in CPU tasks and over twice as fast in graphics benchmarks compared to the previous Ryzen 5000-based Senza model. While not exactly a gaming rig, the Radeon 890M allows for smooth gameplay in e-sports titles (like Counter-Strike 2) and can handle AAA games at lower </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/7825203710022156460'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/7825203710022156460'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/arctic-senza-ai-370-review.html' title='Arctic Senza AI 370 review'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhEXtU36-G08PYw5LjOcHoby0Ke44FZIjpF62fji768zYcf2qF_WCm7il2JG88BD5GztedxjSRznsZ29wwcKuL-GW0gsKsisCmJQYDd7-XNRtCe0cNG54EuQ1xRO2-XX7yba6SeYi48w5zuY1x-Ocok0Kl_JDL8AZ9fYIGdbRnU8nDb6Rh2H7WFQ0k6wac/s72-w400-h225-c/senza3.webp" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-209262557993181940</id><published>2026-03-19T14:17:00.005+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-19T14:27:03.799+01:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>First fanless AMD Ryzen AI computer</title><summary type="text">Arctic&#39;s new Senza PC&amp;nbsp;is powered by the mighty AMD Ryzen AI 9 HX 370, and is virtually invisible.&amp;nbsp;The Senza PC is designed to mount discreetly beneath a desk to maximize workspace and legroom. It features a unique passive cooling system with a surprisingly large heatsink, ensuring completely silent operation and a maintenance-free design with no moving parts. The system also features a </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/209262557993181940'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/209262557993181940'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/first-fanless-amd-ryzen-ai-computer.html' title='First fanless AMD Ryzen AI computer'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj8DZ0S_OGgTxAbT7Pc_EtM7XGSUt3zxC0wm3Rkz1phyphenhyphenX7YrlhKWmKiLwhTtoM6hYqlRzGrx2-c96u0kmW72lvof6pzMjl9KrAEr1J6Q_W77MPEPdc0BDs-s4xaH-C5EcAPe4kwsHvsze2Z2L0Vmg1In_zD7LvLAIgq1vwttRWtcLQ53qfXcjGch0ZiNis/s72-w400-h200-c/Senza_AI_370_Comparison_2.3.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-6334572174413654861</id><published>2026-03-18T00:10:00.001+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-18T00:10:44.618+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Once that shrill little fan finally gets on your last nerve</title><summary type="text">Source: Yukino Song&amp;nbsp;</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/6334572174413654861'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/6334572174413654861'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/once-that-shrill-little-fan-finally.html' title='Once that shrill little fan finally gets on your last nerve'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjyhmdHSeJbz-Fhc2VPYh2PJ-t9QbQyw_snOZfoKydVmesY-zHYA8B4u9z0Bkp4_0XvZn86LdjNH5vGZJBcZelzIxhYXWYL2wm70WNC9Z1A32h-grrMIAbLJkIAFWTzDEYXYyL6aQ3X4QKdJ88u9-mKR-Dp5r4jytxwMo75P4fOAUcJczlRIQwTEG2WYu4/s72-w422-h563-c/DIY2.jpeg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-5954664978043021054</id><published>2026-03-17T00:04:00.002+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-17T00:06:29.018+01:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Arctic"/><title type='text'>Stylish and slim 14600T build</title><summary type="text">Remember this unique build from 2024? Kazuki is back with another impressively slim and compact system. &quot;This time, fins of Arctic Alpine 11 Passive has been trimmed to fit inside the case, instead of cutting the panel of the case to allow exposure of the fins outside the case. I was worried that it might not have sufficient length to dissipate heat well, but to my pleasant surprise, Arctic </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5954664978043021054'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5954664978043021054'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/stylish-and-slim-14500t-build.html' title='Stylish and slim 14600T build'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiEmwtEx2HUxiRb3yCRwA0Z4__vNC-0KqQskHh_1GvTnZ_wO9NEpWZyP5VZpQ-qFaY4212a8-HdbrGvau-UAhDFmccV1rxMrBXFewkXxP3HvSpPZiyJuWJ5HqBF7kcZ6W6EtvXtyPWNL-qGW6OHTjBpUiSa_s-c5EE5wACFMN8gDZQWFAQBpjIyD-FQux8/s72-c/NFC4.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-5679372434427656674</id><published>2026-03-16T00:02:00.001+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-16T00:02:41.321+01:00</updated><title type='text'>The NUC 16 Pro is a powerhouse</title><summary type="text">Courtesy of ASUS</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5679372434427656674'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/5679372434427656674'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/the-nuc-16-pro-is-powerhouse.html' title='The NUC 16 Pro is a powerhouse'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://img.youtube.com/vi/efJD-Bra7nY/default.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-2954927097238852712</id><published>2026-03-13T00:14:00.005+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-13T18:08:34.115+01:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="ASUS"/><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="NUC"/><title type='text'>The NUC 16 Pro is available</title><summary type="text">This new iteration is powered by the Intel Core Ultra Series 3 processors (Panther Lake architecture using Intel&#39;s 18A process node). It features a robust array of connectivity options, including the latest Thunderbolt and Wi-Fi standards, making it a versatile hub for home, professional use, or edge computing. Designed for 24/7 reliability, the&amp;nbsp;Core Ultra 7 356H model is now listed for&amp;nbsp</summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2954927097238852712'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/2954927097238852712'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/the-nuc-16-pro-is-available.html' title='The NUC 16 Pro is available'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgmBysSCD1T5V1SD176fwj8dHHH7JjOtBBt5zKh3oQmkwiSJniGlXiVPM1p3r7jKAoj1rBMIjtsE_1LV4IxdsvZFnyc9Q5mK7-zX-zpgWG8z8kzHuaZbXRGz28m50fVsx9OsLrngYrnZCcaj7rwIJK3gQ6PDEherbII4dnlQXzj0pYiSI8SNrovjWebrWE/s72-w400-h240-c/nuc1.jpg" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-3998004339323629218</id><published>2026-03-12T15:24:00.002+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-12T15:25:37.162+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Passive RTX 4070 mod</title><summary type="text">The core of the mod is a single-slot RTX 4070 &quot;Laptop-on-Desktop&quot; GPU. These cards are often sourced from Chinese markets (like Taobao). They use the power-efficient RTX 4070 mobile chip soldered onto a custom desktop PCIe PCB. This redditor removed the original small, loud fan and adapted the massive Palit KalmX heatsink to fit, achieving solid gaming performance in a system with zero moving </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/3998004339323629218'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/3998004339323629218'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/passive-rtx-4070-mod.html' title='Passive RTX 4070 mod'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjkiNyTkaCO3_GnjxWAO4xFfIRPIFoTO7r4iW9h-DE6-FeVlHcS3g9CQ0faSXuwOFV2LHQVbBJuGSmRJI8RYO6oQB5OE1MPY1rye5W1kCP67N8kgRgX4LAU991OeXPGQ8EWqT_sKIYRVsm478jOzpb3dWSHvLVUMPWoIy0yAvHacJcSMuZKGPFMSSq2b8s/s72-c/KalmX2.webp" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-8387529092221534073</id><published>2026-03-11T12:27:00.001+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-11T12:33:29.862+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Akasa unveils Pascal MX</title><summary type="text">At the heart of the Pascal MX is Akasa&#39;s patented spring-loaded CPU mounting system, which maintains consistent, uniform contact pressure across all supported sockets (Intel® LGA1851, LGA1700, and LGA1200). This enables the same chassis to support Intel® Core™ processors from 10th-14th Generation and the latest Intel® Core™ Ultra (15th Gen) processors, all at up to 65W TDP. Heat from the CPU and </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/8387529092221534073'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/8387529092221534073'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/akasa-unveils-pascal-mx.html' title='Akasa unveils Pascal MX'/><author><name>Unknown</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='https://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgaHBIwBD1H7WBZXHtgJrE0c6nQddp3Kwa5U2SorRgOgw4hyo23lrF0v2r-dxEv1ekA0HQR67M4D8xgzKx0PvQhVWSC8svIOPmGgbshU0RlZfT4WXRmfp3b9krCmieo6Xs8LZqGnJly0ACy-SfcgoNmWFIkH-y46OI6lQE_ukxKAp2r-_UjfBSMOC94dM4/s72-w400-h400-c/pascal1.png" height="72" width="72"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-5174233475887084833.post-1192915595542822845</id><published>2026-03-10T00:14:00.001+01:00</published><updated>2026-03-10T00:14:08.224+01:00</updated><title type='text'>Portable mini workstation</title><summary type="text">This compact and highly capable mini workstation is powered by an Intel Core i7-1165G7 processor and 32GB of RAM, making it ideal for noise-sensitive environments like home offices or studios. It features a robust full-metal chassis that acts as a heat sink for the 28W CPU. The system supports 8K/4K dual-display outputs through its Iris Xe Graphics. Equipped with a 1TB NVMe SSD and WiFi 6 / </summary><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/1192915595542822845'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/5174233475887084833/posts/default/1192915595542822845'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.fanlesstech.com/2026/03/por